   "source": [
    "# Baybayin OCR Training Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook reproduces the end-to-end workflow we automated earlier:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Ensure the working tree is on the project root (`baybayin_project`).\n",
    "2. (Optionally) tighten `.box` coordinates so each glyph box hugs the character.\n",
    "3. Launch the training pipeline via `run_training.sh` with your preferred dataset and parameters.\n",
    "4. Summarise training progress from the generated `training.log`.\n",
    "5. Evaluate the resulting model against holdout samples that were not part of training.\n",
    "6. Produce visualisations to inspect predictions.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Tip:** Each code cell calls the existing Python or shell scripts that already live in this repository. Feel free to tweak paths or parameters before running."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    \"\"\"%%bash\n",
    "# 1. Quick sanity-check: show current working directory and list key scripts.\n",
    "echo \"Working directory: $PWD\"\n",
    "ls -1 adjust_box_coordinates.py run_training.sh evaluate_holdout.py generate_holdout_visuals.py |> sed 's/^/ - /'\n",
    \"\"\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Configure Paths\n",
    "Edit the block below to point to the dataset you want to train with, the output model name, and the location of the traineddata directory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "parameters"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Feel free to modify these variables before running later cells.\n",
    "DATASET_FOR_TRAINING = \"kaggle_dataset_corrected_full\"  # directory with single-glyph .tif/.box/.gt.txt\n",
    "MODEL_NAME = \"bay_full_corrected\"                       # name used by run_training.sh and output traineddata\n",
    "MAX_ITERATIONS = 10000                                   # training iterations (use more for large datasets)\n",
    "TESSDATA_DIR = \"tesseract_training/data\"               # location where traineddata files are written\n",
    "\n",
    "# Optional: directory containing holdout samples (same format as training set)\n",
    "HOLDOUT_SOURCE = \"kaggle_dataset\"                       # must include .tif/.box/.gt.txt pairs not used in training\n",
    "\n",
    "# Directory to store evaluation visuals\n",
    "HOLDOUT_VIS_DIR = \"visualizations/holdout_manual\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Training dataset:\", DATASET_FOR_TRAINING)\n",
    "print(\"Model name:\", MODEL_NAME)\n",
    "print(\"Max iterations:\", MAX_ITERATIONS)\n",
    "print(\"Traineddata dir:\", TESSDATA_DIR)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## (Optional) Tighten Bounding Boxes\n",
    "Run this cell if you want to recompute `.box` coordinates so each glyph is tightly enclosed. Skip if your dataset is already cleaned."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    \"\"\"%%bash\n",
    "# Only run if you really want to overwrite existing box coordinates.\n",
    "python3 adjust_box_coordinates.py \\\n",
    "    --dataset \"$DATASET_FOR_TRAINING\" \\\n",
    "    --min-pixels 4\n",
    \"\"\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Launch Training\n",
    "This invokes the same `run_training.sh` script we've been using. It will:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Clone `tesstrain` / `langdata_lstm` if needed.\n",
    "2. Copy & clean ground truth into `tesseract_training/data/<MODEL_NAME>-ground-truth`.\n",
    "3. Download the base English model (`eng.traineddata`).\n",
    "4. Run the Tesstrain `make training` step.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** Training can take a long time on large datasets. Monitor the console output or tail the generated `training.log`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    \"\"\"%%bash\n",
    "set -e\n",
    "MODEL_NAME=\"$MODEL_NAME\" \\\n",
    "SOURCE_DATASET=\"$DATASET_FOR_TRAINING\" \\\n",
    "MAX_ITERATIONS=\"$MAX_ITERATIONS\" \\\n",
    "./run_training.sh\n",
    \"\"\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summarise Training Log\n",
    "After the run, `tesseract_training/data/<MODEL_NAME>/training.log` contains progress snapshots. The helper below mirrors the summary we used earlier."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import json\n",
    "import pathlib\n",
    "import re\n",
    "\n",
    "log_path = pathlib.Path(\"tesseract_training/data\") / MODEL_NAME / \"training.log\"\n",
    "print(\"Looking for log at\", log_path)\n",
    "if not log_path.exists():\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(\"training.log not found – check that training completed successfully.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "pattern = re.compile(r\"At iteration (\\d+)/(\\d+)/(\\d+), Mean rms=([0-9.]+)%, delta=([0-9.]+)%, char train=([0-9.]+)%, word train=([0-9.]+)%, skip ratio=([0-9.]+)%\")\n",
    "checkpoints = {}\n",
    "with log_path.open() as f:\n",
    "    for line in f:\n",
    "        m = pattern.search(line)\n",
    "        if not m:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        iteration = int(m.group(1))\n",
    "        bucket = max(1000, (iteration // 1000) * 1000)\n",
    "        if bucket not in checkpoints or iteration < checkpoints[bucket][\"iter\"]:\n",
    "            checkpoints[bucket] = {\n",
    "                \"iter\": iteration,\n",
    "                \"mean_rms\": float(m.group(4)),\n",
    "                \"delta\": float(m.group(5)),\n",
    "                \"char_error\": float(m.group(6)),\n",
    "                \"word_error\": float(m.group(7)),\n",
    "            }\n",
    "\n",
    "summary = [{\"bucket\": bucket, **data} for bucket, data in sorted(checkpoints.items())]\n",
    "print(json.dumps(summary, indent=2))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Evaluate on Holdout Samples\n",
    "Use `evaluate_holdout.py` to run the new model against images that were not part of training. Adjust `--limit`/`--offset` to control how many samples to test."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    \"\"\"%%bash\n",
    "python3 evaluate_holdout.py \\\n",
    "  --full-set \"$HOLDOUT_SOURCE\" \\\n",
    "  --train-set \"$DATASET_FOR_TRAINING\" \\\n",
    "  --tessdata-dir \"$TESSDATA_DIR\" \\\n",
    "  --model \"$MODEL_NAME\" \\\n",
    "  --limit 200\n",
    \"\"\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualise Predictions\n",
    "Generate PNGs that overlay bounding boxes and include both ground-truth and predicted text. Helpful for manual inspection."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    \"\"\"%%bash\n",
    "python3 generate_holdout_visuals.py \\\n",
    "  --full-set \"$HOLDOUT_SOURCE\" \\\n",
    "  --train-set \"$DATASET_FOR_TRAINING\" \\\n",
    "  --tessdata-dir \"$TESSDATA_DIR\" \\\n",
    "  --model \"$MODEL_NAME\" \\\n",
    "  --limit 10 \\\n",
    "  --offset 0 \\\n",
    "  --output-dir \"$HOLDOUT_VIS_DIR\"\n",
    \"\"\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Next Steps\n",
    "- Increase `MAX_ITERATIONS` or use the full dataset for stronger models.\n",
    "- Run `make evaluation MODEL_NAME=...` inside `tesseract_training` for Tesstrain's built-in eval workflow.\n",
    "- Analyse per-character error by extending `evaluate_holdout.py`.\n",
    "- Automate the pipeline further by wrapping these commands in your own scripts."
   ]
  }
